Marrying someone from another country has been a big business in Nauru.

Many Australian and European sailors would routinely land in the island and pay good whelks (money) to have fun 1 night stands with Nauruan women.

Australian diaries also have plenty of mentions about Nauruan women and how big their breasts would become even with pregnancy and breastfeeding. There even was the practice of Australian UN shipping assistant’s wives going on holiday to Nauru to “ get pregnant “.

One important reason Nauruan got to be so easy (whereas now it could take months to get an Australian resident visa) was that in the late 1980s, Nauru used to self-fund the whole UN presence, including their wives and families back home (i.e. Washinton DC) via the visas.

Getting a Nauruan wife could be risky, especially if the bride moves to the husband’s country, as plenty of these marriages ended in divorce – and the question of children involved was often very difficult :
